cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.AI 

This paper is about word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of these embeddings in machine learning tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of web data, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper's focus on tweet data and sentiment analysis could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
